{"id": "EUVD-2025-124909", "enisaUuid": "85e6d165-442d-33d4-840f-0ccf7a306d3a", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nx86/mm: Fix SMP ordering in switch_mm_irqs_off()\n\nStephen noted that it is possible to not have an smp_mb() between\nthe loaded_mm store and the tlb_gen load in switch_mm(), meaning the\nordering against flush_tlb_mm_range() goes out the window, and it\nbecomes possible for switch_mm() to not observe a recent tlb_gen\nupdate and fail to flush the TLBs.\n\n[ dhansen: merge conflict fixed by Ingo ]", "datePublished": "2025-11-12T10:53:49", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-01T06:19:29", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0fe5e3f5fb75c5d88dad24dece3ee75e9d87adeb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/83b0177a6c4889b3a6e865da5e21b2c9d97d0551", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40174"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40174"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "073f874a-5987-358a-b5a3-93aaba01ca83", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18-rc2"}, {"id": "10d29ff4-06b2-3b2f-ab0b-3732c86f146c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.14"}, {"id": "7306a030-6d47-3802-8aa7-6999606ba2a1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "209954cbc7d0ce1a190fc725d20ce303d74d2680 <83b0177a6c4889b3a6e865da5e21b2c9d97d0551"}, {"id": "793b1192-c8a9-30be-ae0b-6830302c2681", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "209954cbc7d0ce1a190fc725d20ce303d74d2680 <0fe5e3f5fb75c5d88dad24dece3ee75e9d87adeb"}, {"id": "7e0b0f75-0153-3490-b645-b57201cab45b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "c4af8a8e-d47b-3970-80d5-13e7eb58ce18", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "d1841d0a-2ff1-306f-a131-654242ed3428", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17.5"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "1da1ebf2-f289-3c67-9c34-d9ed397be127", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploit